50. Construct a PHP script to lower-case and upper-case, all elements in an array.
CODE:
<?php
// Sample array
$words = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry", "Mango"];

// Convert all to lowercase
$lowercaseArray = array_map('strtolower', $words);

// Convert all to uppercase
$uppercaseArray = array_map('strtoupper', $words);

// Output results
echo "Original Array: ";
print_r($words);

echo "\nLowercase Array: ";
print_r($lowercaseArray);

echo "\nUppercase Array: ";
print_r($uppercaseArray);
?>
OUTPUT:
Original Array: Array ( [0] => Apple [1] => Banana [2] => Cherry [3] => Mango )
Lowercase Array: Array ( [0] => apple [1] => banana [2] => cherry [3] => mango )
Uppercase Array: Array ( [0] => APPLE [1] => BANANA [2] => CHERRY [3] => MANGO )
